    },
    {
      "content": "A data disk that can be attached to an Azure VM for persistent storage.",
      "pos": [
        7058,
        7129
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Prerequisites",
      "pos": [
        7135,
        7148
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To migrate your VMs, you'll need:",
      "pos": [
        7150,
        7183
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An Azure subscription, a storage account, and a container in that storage account to copy your VHD to.",
      "pos": [
        7187,
        7289
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that the destination storage account can be a Standard or Premium Storage account depending on your requirement.",
      "pos": [
        7290,
        7407
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A tool to generalize VHD if you plan to create multiple VM instances from it.",
      "pos": [
        7411,
        7488
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, sysprep for Windows or virt-sysprep for Ubuntu.",
      "pos": [
        7489,
        7549
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A tool to upload the VHD file to the Storage account.",
      "pos": [
        7553,
        7606
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>AzCopy<ept id=\"p1\">](storage-use-azcopy.md)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure storage explorer<ept id=\"p2\">](http://blogs.msdn.com/b/windowsazurestorage/archive/2014/03/11/windows-azure-storage-explorers-2014.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        7607,
        7786
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This guide describes copying your VHD using the AzCopy tool.",
      "pos": [
        7787,
        7847
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> For optimal performance, copy your VHD by running one of these tools from an Azure VM that is in the same region as the destination storage account.",
      "pos": [
        7852,
        8013
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you are copying a VHD from an Azure VM in a different region, your performance may be slower.",
      "pos": [
        8014,
        8110
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For copying a large amount of data over limited bandwidth, consider using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Azure Import/Export service<ept id=\"p1\">](storage-import-export-service.md)</ept> to transfer your data by shipping hard disk drives to an Azure datacenter.",
      "pos": [
        8115,
        8341
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use the Azure Import/Export service to copy data to a standard storage account only.",
      "pos": [
        8342,
        8434
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once the data is in your standard storage account, you can use either the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Copy Blob API<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dd894037.aspx)</ept> or AzCopy to transfer the data to your premium storage account.",
      "pos": [
        8435,
        8644
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that Microsoft Azure only supports fixed size VHD files.",
      "pos": [
        8650,
        8711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "VHDX files or dynamic VHDs are not supported.",
      "pos": [
        8712,
        8757
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have a dynamic VHD, you can convert it to fixed size using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Convert-VHD<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/hh848454.aspx)</ept> cmdlet.",
