    },
    {
      "content": "Generalized Operating System VHD to create multiple VM instances",
      "pos": [
        9005,
        9069
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you are uploading a VHD that will be used to create multiple generic Azure VM instances, you must first generalize VHD using a sysprep utility.",
      "pos": [
        9071,
        9217
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This applies to a VHD that is on-premise or in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        9218,
        9275
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Sysprep removes any machine specific information from the VHD.",
      "pos": [
        9276,
        9338
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.IMPORTANT]</ph> Take a snapshot or backup your VM before generalizing it.",
      "pos": [
        9341,
        9416
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Running sysprep will delete the VM instance.",
      "pos": [
        9417,
        9461
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Follow steps below to sysprep a Windows OS VHD.",
      "pos": [
        9462,
        9509
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that running the Sysprep command will require you to shut down the virtual machine.",
      "pos": [
        9510,
        9598
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about Sysprep, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Sysprep Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/hh825209.aspx)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Sysprep Technical Reference<ept id=\"p2\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc766049(v=ws.10).aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        9599,
        9804
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Open a Command Prompt window as an administrator.",
      "pos": [
        9809,
        9858
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enter the following command to open Sysprep:",
      "pos": [
        9862,
        9906
      ]
